{"id":34966,"date":"2021-01-17T16:53:33","date_gmt":"2021-01-17T12:53:33","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34966"},"modified":"2021-01-18T14:44:29","modified_gmt":"2021-01-18T10:44:29","slug":"aishah-humility-deathbed","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/17\/aishah-humility-deathbed\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Death: Aisha\u2019s Godfearing humility on her deathbed"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Abi Mulaykah reported: Ibn Abbas asked permission to see Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, before her death while she was overcome with suffering. Aisha said, \u201cI am afraid he will praise me.\u201d It was said, \u201cHe is the cousin of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and a prominent Muslim.\u201d Aisha said, \u201cGive him permission.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cHow do you find yourself?\u201d Aisha said, \u201cI am good, if I fear Allah.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cYou are good, if Allah wills. You are the wife of the Messenger of Allah. He married no virgin besides you. Your innocence was revealed from heaven.\u201d Ibn al-Zubayr entered after him and Aisha said, \u201cIbn Abbas visited and praised me. I wish I was a thing forgotten!\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4573<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064f\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0643\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0633\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0623\u0652\u0630\u064e\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0628\u0652\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0648\u0652\u062a\u0650\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631